CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 6, 1959, pg. 1 reads: "Removing Debris - With a bulldozer and other wrecking vehicles, a crew of workmen on Monday were removing the remains of the three-story building at 616 Protectory Pl., which collapsed last Friday evening. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Two men watching collapsed building being removed by bulldozer, 616 Protectory Place, Hill District
